# API Flow Diagram

**Purpose**: Complete request flow from client through FastAPI middleware, routing, dependency injection, service layer, agents, to data stores.

---

## Request Flow Summary

```
Client Request
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    MIDDLEWARE STACK (Order Matters)             │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 1. CORSMiddleware          │ Origin validation, preflight       │
│ 2. RateLimitMiddleware     │ Token bucket (local) + Sliding     │
│                            │ window (Redis), adaptive limits    │
│ 3. LoggingMiddleware       │ Correlation IDs, structured JSON,  │
│                            │ PII redaction, security events     │
│ 4. SecurityMiddleware      │ JWT RS256 validation, API Key      │
│                            │ bcrypt, RBAC (Admin/Analyst/Viewer)│
│ 5. CompressionMiddleware   │ Gzip/Brotli, minimum size 500B     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      ROUTE MATCHING                              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ /api/v1/research/*    → ResearchRouter (Phase 7)                │
│ /api/v1/watchlists/*  → WatchlistRouter (Phase 7)               │
│ /api/v1/approval/*    → ApprovalRouter (Phase 7)                │
│ /api/v1/reports/*     → ReportRouter (Phase 7)                  │
│ /api/v1/copilot/*     → CopilotRouter (Phase 8)                 │
│ /health/*             → HealthRouter (Phase 6)                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  DEPENDENCY INJECTION                            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ get_current_user()    → JWT validation → User object            │
│ require_permission()  → RBAC check (20+ permissions)            │
│ get_session()         → AsyncSession (SQLAlchemy 2.0)           │
│ get_settings()        → Typed Settings (Pydantic, 80+ fields)   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      SERVICE LAYER                               │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Research Endpoints    → ManagerAgent + WorkflowOrchestrator     │
│                       → ResearchPlannerAgent                    │
│ Copilot Endpoints     → CopilotAgent (Intent → Plan → Execute)  │
│                       → ToolRegistry (15 tools, 14 categories)  │
│                       → CollaborationCoordinator (10 signals)   │
│                       → DecisionEngine (6-step reasoning)       │
│                       → ExplainabilityEngine (evidence, risks)  │
│                       → EnhancedMemoryStore (5 scopes)          │
│                       → LLMRouter (9 models, 4 goals, adaptive) │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      AGENT LAYER (14 Agents)                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ All agents implement BaseWorkerAgent:                           │
│   async def run(company: str, context: Dict) -> Dict[str, Any]  │
│                                                                 │
│ ManagerAgent orchestrates all 14 agents via registry            │
│ WorkflowOrchestrator: topological sort → parallel waves         │
│ ResearchPlannerAgent: LLM-driven dynamic planning               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    DATA & INFRASTRUCTURE                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ PostgreSQL (27 tables)  ← All persistent state                 │
│ ChromaDB (5 collections) ← Vector embeddings (BGE-M3, 1024-dim) │
│ Redis (Cache/Sessions/RateLimit) ← High-speed operations       │
│ SEC EDGAR (10 req/s) ← Filings                                 │
│ 6 News Providers ← Multi-source news                            │
│ Market Data APIs ← Yahoo, AlphaVantage, Finnhub                 │
│ OpenRouter (9 models) ← LLM inference                           │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

